[
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.1",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "The proverbs of Solomon the son of David, king of Israel;",
    "hash": "136a945345483840884cd52096e29dfca783bb90c7c42489c3cad1ba0a0eb384"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.2",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "To know wisdom and instruction; to perceive the words of understanding;",
    "hash": "0adbcb96f824b46d31d1ea2e827020c46f6ca0991533ca5b229c286526279e71"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.3",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "To receive the instruction of wisdom, justice, and judgment, and equity; {equity: Heb. equities}",
    "hash": "dfc0184189337f4c30d3e58ab94a1888b00594096c681b8beccf262435a7e1e3"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.4",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "To give subtilty to the simple, to the young man knowledge and discretion. {discretion: or, advisement}",
    "hash": "5d8dcf7e0dfcfdd4440a73e174a53fe4574aa50d3a3c5a9d79709ff6dd5e44ff"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.5",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "A wise {man} will hear, and will increase learning; and a man of understanding shall attain unto wise counsels:",
    "hash": "4de095ec800d16f9955d2f2d2cbfb422406518d9f875ab49fd341723154622c3"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.6",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "To understand a proverb, and the interpretation; the words of the wise, and their dark sayings. {the interpretation: or, an eloquent speech}",
    "hash": "7a5c3def2cc2a932644100d7dc7ffe181871d27633c385981fd4e5f25bbbb7e3"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.7",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "The fear of the LORD {is} the beginning of knowledge: {but} fools despise wisdom and instruction. {the beginning: or, the principal part}",
    "hash": "d8ed6f806f6142e0b58912cab721ef49bd6f7a9cb621609333bac9b8074a099f"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.8",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "My son, hear the instruction of thy father, and forsake not the law of thy mother:",
    "hash": "7b22f1656e318f3dc1f3a1faed21c097920fb7824ff480690b6e9a7d6505bb43"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.9",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "For they {shall be} an ornament of grace unto thy head, and chains about thy neck. {an...: Heb. an adding}",
    "hash": "7149da57899e9b296096ac3533284a4696611fd3b2ebb2b171a63e2e25aa0bdc"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.10",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "My son, if sinners entice thee, consent thou not.",
    "hash": "64e25a6995b00fca6d1bdef403fb58cce659730ac0f3836fa82abe3184c00120"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.11",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "If they say, Come with us, let us lay wait for blood, let us lurk privily for the innocent without cause:",
    "hash": "4bfec3992988c63425a6dc568222aa9bb4d50ec42aca61f4cfe308b9f99ae351"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.12",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Let us swallow them up alive as the grave; and whole, as those that go down into the pit:",
    "hash": "e84087e23009c86e1efca25f29c989a2de2d23570589533a9be756c817c99dba"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.13",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "We shall find all precious substance, we shall fill our houses with spoil:",
    "hash": "f0649352aebfa77576338224d1176d89e51d80e9d8c1cb41c78bd5c08338eb37"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.14",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Cast in thy lot among us; let us all have one purse:",
    "hash": "cf92307738d358eedb115227310118b360c5948ca87b727aa512577ec185e98a"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.15",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "My son, walk not thou in the way with them; refrain thy foot from their path:",
    "hash": "41fc342b8fbc2f2a4c2c206c089cacc40eb0165e1bc2e2f2370c7483c9901936"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.16",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "For their feet run to evil, and make haste to shed blood.",
    "hash": "9040a09fffc7278efc0153d8e91366e6a279bd34ce66c1084c921194b7a8389f"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.17",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Surely in vain the net is spread in the sight of any bird. {in the...: Heb. in the eyes of every thing that hath a wing}",
    "hash": "bcf531083382a898c860126fac777731e3228de40fbd0fd04c69511081da303f"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.18",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "And they lay wait for their {own} blood; they lurk privily for their {own} lives.",
    "hash": "68019fb71a566d125e57632f993817796129715a10c91838751aef23dcb9b432"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.19",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "So {are} the ways of every one that is greedy of gain; {which} taketh away the life of the owners thereof.",
    "hash": "6060e75e00e45a14fd579567c77ccb63ac29e9966b6db5fe4f8d6ab01c207fb5"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.20",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Wisdom crieth without; she uttereth her voice in the streets: {Wisdom: Heb. Wisdoms, that is, Excellent wisdom}",
    "hash": "cd1a0a56883cce5ac3c69026a7fb1d92815fa4057574e2892fab5bb108708f50"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.21",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "She crieth in the chief place of concourse, in the openings of the gates: in the city she uttereth her words, {saying},",
    "hash": "30e5667c8ee299bdf4734010234bed94397afd6a40feecd53ff65d2a45849134"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.22",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "How long, ye simple ones, will ye love simplicity? and the scorners delight in their scorning, and fools hate knowledge?",
    "hash": "31fbc154b78cf6d2483c81785baeab527ae7e2da25775d2577ce716d557883fa"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.23",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "Turn you at my reproof: behold, I will pour out my spirit unto you, I will make known my words unto you.",
    "hash": "2b5799d3a59f4ddf57755fd190f3d196ae550ca1d68052cc42382a2d64413477"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.24",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Because I have called, and ye refused; I have stretched out my hand, and no man regarded;",
    "hash": "60cb17c8124a98ce0b59a60539f742fc3f09a8aa36618eb0f1b16a728ef0fc85"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.25",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "But ye have set at nought all my counsel, and would none of my reproof:",
    "hash": "ea29dc02c801512e1d5007000deca989d1c91de21d228b161d85a2396b8b401d"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.26",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "I also will laugh at your calamity; I will mock when your fear cometh;",
    "hash": "1bfb3a14bddfc07eaa46b6f7262ea561e91e1c555ecc47a016d4012dcecbf491"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.27",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "When your fear cometh as desolation, and your destruction cometh as a whirlwind; when distress and anguish cometh upon you.",
    "hash": "bef07f3d3798fdb6dab1187fffca97a25ad56150a10f8ebce884ac31143af7b7"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.28",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "Then shall they call upon me, but I will not answer; they shall seek me early, but they shall not find me:",
    "hash": "9ea9f65491b8c5514a2e9be1bbf35c4b40f1f357bed403abf1b18e003807e082"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.29",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "For that they hated knowledge, and did not choose the fear of the LORD:",
    "hash": "31a470da6efeb0f38b1cacf7c15bebff05af25f60b2006eed27f53b94e246a39"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.30",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "They would none of my counsel: they despised all my reproof.",
    "hash": "a2bcd76f6b67424a4ff6ca70e3da1068088192c81fbc93b6afe8ba62ca46a4ed"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.31",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "Therefore shall they eat of the fruit of their own way, and be filled with their own devices.",
    "hash": "d9f4fd00fa6714e56a964e237cf4f31c3c14faeca3858d08de0726f82f5833b3"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.32",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "For the turning away of the simple shall slay them, and the prosperity of fools shall destroy them. {turning...: or, ease of the simple}",
    "hash": "7d266d7f4c3e64bcc7d57a1dfe3ddbe02b52c5e6ce88a59bde830d9558df7853"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.1.33",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "But whoso hearkeneth unto me shall dwell safely, and shall be quiet from fear of evil.",
    "hash": "89ab6d2df7867dce76e10f23bf834e67fca94821bdc6ee704f2a03d992b45bdb"
  }
]